{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 03:52:16.908537", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nExecutive summary\n- The network is partially degraded. All services via the 10.2.x.x distribution block operate normally, but the 10.1.1.x access block is effectively isolated: hosts there are not obtaining IP addresses via DHCP and cannot reach core/server networks.\n- Primary fault localized to router_dist_1_1: FRR (OSPF) is not running, leaving it without routes to the server farm (10.200.0.0/24). As a consequence, DHCP relay cannot reach the DHCP server, and hosts on 10.1.1.0/24 do not get IPs and have no L3 reachability.\n\nObserved anomalies and impact\n- host_1_1_1_1 has no IP address and no routes:\n  - Interface eth0 is UP but has no inet address; ip route is empty.\n  - Pings from host_1_1_1_1 to DNS/load-balancer/web servers fail with “Network is unreachable.”\n  - Curl to web99.local and web0.local from host_1_1_1_1 shows near-zero timings (indicating immediate failure; no DNS/connection established).\n- router_dist_1_1 cannot reach server networks:\n  - Pings from router_dist_1_1 to dhcp_server, dns_server, load_balancer fail with “Network is unreachable.”\n  - Its routing table shows only connected routes (10.1.1.0/24 on br0 and 172.16.0.6/31 on eth0); no learned routes to 10.200.0.0/24 or elsewhere.\n- FRR state across the fabric:\n  - router_dist_1_1: FRR service is inactive (dead).\n  - router_dist_2_1, router_core_1/2/3, server_access_router: FRR is active (running).\n- Healthy reference path (10.2.1.0/24):\n  - host_2_1_1_1 has a valid DHCP lease (10.2.1.21/24) and default route via 10.2.1.1.\n  - host_2_1_1_1 can ping DNS (10.200.0.2) and load_balancer (10.200.0.7) with 0% loss.\n  - Curl to web99.local and web0.local from host_2_1_1_1 shows normal resolution and ~1.0–1.18 s total times, indicating end-to-end service availability for this block.\n\nLocalization\n- Faulty device: router_dist_1_1.\n  - Evidence: FRR inactive; no OSPF-learned routes; cannot reach core/server networks.\n- Affected segment: Access/distribution block for 10.1.1.0/24 (switch_access_1_1_1 and hosts behind it), as exemplified by host_1_1_1_1 lacking DHCP and IP connectivity.\n- Unaffected segments: Distribution block 2_1 (10.2.1.0/24) and server farm side; core routers and server_access_router show FRR running and paths operational.\n\nRoot cause analysis\n- Immediate cause: FRR is stopped on router_dist_1_1, breaking OSPF adjacency and route propagation on that node.\n- Downstream effect: Without OSPF routes to 10.200.0.0/24 (and likely no default route), router_dist_1_1 cannot forward DHCP relay traffic to the centralized DHCP server at 10.200.0.8. Hosts on 10.1.1.0/24 therefore fail to receive IP configuration, leaving them with no L3 reachability to DNS/web services.\n- Corroboration:\n  - host_1_1_1_1 shows no IP or routes.\n  - router_dist_1_1 has only connected routes; pings to server side return “Network is unreachable.”\n  - Other routers’ FRR services are running, and the 10.2.1.0/24 block functions normally end-to-end, isolating the issue to the 10.1.1.0/24 distribution router.\n\nAdditional notes\n- L2 on the access side appears up (host_1_1_1_1 eth0 is UP). The failure mode (no DHCP/IP, network unreachable) aligns with the upstream router lacking routing and, hence, a functional DHCP relay path.\n- No evidence observed of backend web servers being directly accessible from hosts; due to lack of L3 on 10.1.1.0/24 the policy there couldn’t be verified, but the healthy 10.2.1.0/24 path behaves as expected via the load balancer.\n\nSummary of key evidence (selected)\n- host_1_1_1_1 ip/route: no IP, empty route table; pings/curl fail (network unreachable/instant failure).\n- router_dist_1_1 FRR: inactive (dead); no routes beyond connected; pings to 10.200.0.0/24 unreachables.\n- host_2_1_1_1: valid DHCP (10.2.1.21/24), default route via 10.2.1.1, pings to DNS/LB succeed; curl to web services succeeds.\n- FRR on core and server side: active (running).", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 36481, "output_tokens": 3710, "total_tokens": 40191, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 35968}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 2560}}}
